  "description": [
    "DELAWARES OLDEST CONSECUTIVELY PUBLISHED NEWSPAPER HOME COUNTY AND STATE NEWS OF TIMELY INTEREST WHOLE NO 5185 SMYRNA DELAWARE THURSDAY MORNING FEBRUARY 25 1954 VOLUME 100 NO 35 VOTERS NAME PRICE WILSON ALDERMAN APPOINTED _ Richard C Price and John E Wilson IH were the victors in the contest for two seats on Town Council in the offyear municipal election held here Monday There 357 votes cast of which 7 were thrown out Mr Price re ceived 264 votes Mr Wilson 173 The other candidates were Linden S Doughten who ran a close sec ond to Mr Wilson receiving 161 votes and Richard L Cochran 85 votes John R Jacobs treasurer Richard Price and John E Wilson IH Sworn in As Councilmen Tuesday w I re without opposition received the to tal 357 votes Holdover members of council are Mayor John J Hurd George Blendt and William Staats Take Oaths Of Office Mr Price and Mr Wilson were sworn in at a special meeting of Council Tuesday night in the may ors office Mayor John J Hurd officiated at the ceremony and also swore in Mr Jacobs as treasurer J Austen Deamer judge and Mrs Homer D Hudson clerk present1 ed"
